<br>
Often these attempts to regulate the emotions they are going through can be less than helpful.<br>
<br>
Everquest is one of those. Depressed people tend to withdraw from society; yet, even depressed people need social ties. Playing everquest allows for people who have withdrawn to maintain social ties.<br>
<br>
The problem is that it reinforces a behavior which might feel necessary but ends up causing more pain than helping.<br>
<br>
In EQ if you don't like someone you can put them on ignore. Don't like a situation, you can always walk or run away. Don't like anything? You can log off.<br>
<br>
Basically what it teaches you is the fine art of escapism. Even as you search for social ties and perhaps even find some, it reinforces the desire to escape.<br>
<br>
If you have a problem, get help. Everquest isn't the answer.<br>
<br>
How do you know if you are depressed?<br>
<br>
Major Depressive Disorder, is diagnosed based on the presence of at least 2 weeks of depressed mood or loss of interest, accompanied by at least 4 of the following symptoms: <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Change in appetite or weight (increased or decreased) <br>
Change in sleep (increased or decreased) <br>
Psychomotor retardation or agitation <br>
Fatigue or loss of energy <br>
Feelings of worthlessness or guilt <br>
Difficulty concentrating or indecisiveness <br>
Thoughts of death or suicidal ideation<br>
<br>
<br>
Depression sucks, get help -- it doesn't have to ruin your life.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
